Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim and halve @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (quarter any large mushrooms). Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%ounce}, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @tempura mix{82%g}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, 1/3 cup cold water, and ½ tsp salt. TIP: If needed, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until the mixture reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Stir mushrooms into batter until fully coated.

Divide tempura batter between 2 #medium bowls{}. Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir shrimp into batter in one bowl and mushrooms in other until fully coated.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, use #tongs{} to add coated mushrooms in a single layer. TIP: You may need to work in batches. Cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on the first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on the second side.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt.

Once mushrooms are fried, repeat shallow-frying process with shrimp. TIP: If needed, add more oil to pan before frying shrimp. Cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Using a slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tablepoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with mushrooms and green beans. Drizzle with dynamite sauce and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

Top bowls with shrimp.

== Dynamite Sauce ==

One of our favorite ways to eat our veggies? Giving them the tempura treatment! This sauce is creamy, spicy, sweet, and savory (yes, all those things!)

Combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%ounce}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of @lime juice{} to taste for the dynamite sauce.